Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.41,0:28:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你无法发现两颗小行星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You couldn't find two asteroids more different
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.21,0:28:15.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不同之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.38,0:28:19.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谷神星之前被认为相对潮湿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ceres is thought to be relatively wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.03,0:28:21.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能表面有冰覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps subsurface ices,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.22,0:28:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而另一颗灶神星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the other one, Vesta,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.54,0:28:23.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被认为正好相反\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is thought to be the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.69,0:28:26.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全没有氢氧化物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's completely lacking in hydrated minerals
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:28.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or water ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.16,0:28:31.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它一生都在被如此大程度地加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been heated over its lifetime to such an extent
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.43,0:28:32.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以至于被认为是分层的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it's thought to be layered:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.06,0:28:36.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有类似地球的分层的表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A surface layer, a mantle, and a core
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.12,0:28:37.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有地幔和地核\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much like the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.14,0:28:45.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有这些任务揭示出小行星的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of these missions are revealing that asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.04,0:28:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,组成比我们之前认为的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are made from a much wider assortment of materials
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.82,0:28:48.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更加多元化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than we first realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.78,0:28:53.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星有非常多的种类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a huge variety in asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.15,0:28:56.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些富含铁和镍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of them are iron rich or nickel rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.34,0:28:58.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很像这个哑铃\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}very much like this iron dumbbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.79,0:29:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些很类似这个地球上的岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others are very similar to this earthbound rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.32,0:29:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是石质的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're stony.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.13,0:29:03.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩石构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're rocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.79,0:29:06.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他的由铁类和岩石类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Still others are a combination between the iron type
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.80,0:29:08.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,组合成的类型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the stony type.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.80,0:29:13.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还发现了像碎石堆一样的外来物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've also got exotic things like rubble piles,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.44,0:29:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像这一堆砂砾构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are like having this handful of gravel,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.42,0:29:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但全部都由引力束缚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but if it all were gravitationally bound
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.65,0:29:21.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在大的小行星表面成为一种类型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a big asteroid kind of a form.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.81,0:29:24.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还发现了外太空的彗星残骸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We also have ex-comets.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.81,0:29:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,彗星残骸没有了它们的表面的冰覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And ex-comets have gotten rid of all their ices,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.82,0:29:32.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留给我们这种很好的粒状的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we're left with this fine grain material,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.36,0:29:35.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,感觉像是多孔的绒球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}held in a very porous type of fluff ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.19,0:29:37.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但小行星除了它们的组成外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But asteroids are surprising us in other ways
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.69,0:29:41.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他方面令我们吃惊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}besides their composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.46,0:29:43.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"伽利略"号探测器在前往木星的途中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Galileo mission on its way to Jupiter
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.70,0:29:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过了一颗叫艾达的小行星并且发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}went past an asteroid called Ida and discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.84,0:29:49.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有颗小的卫星就是艾卫\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it had a little tiny moon called Dactyl.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.84,0:29:51.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这真是太令人意外了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was a big surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.74,0:29:55.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在  我们知道这不仅仅是个巧合\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And now, we see that that's not so rare an incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.38,0:29:59.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星确实会有它们自己的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Asteroids do come with their own moons,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.02,0:30:00.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候会有几颗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes several moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.65,0:30:03.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也明白了许多小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're also learning that a lot of asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.72,0:30:05.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是以双星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are traveling in pairs as binaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.44,0:30:08.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至三星的状态存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or even with three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.16,0:30:11.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是很非常新鲜的观察结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's a very new set of observations
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:14.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是需要了解的新事物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and new thing to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.36,0:30:17.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,理解小行星是如何成群的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Knowing how asteroids are grouped
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.44,0:30:18.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是如何构成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and what they're made of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.83,0:30:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅是科学感兴趣的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is more than a matter of scientific interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.64,0:30:25.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象在未来  一颗巨大的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine in the future, that an enormous,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.84,0:30:28.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,致命的小行星向地球袭来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}deadly asteroid is speeding towards earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.34,0:30:30.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果人类还想生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It needs to be deflected
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.53,0:30:33.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就必须让它偏离轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if mankind is going to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.08,0:30:35.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果我们不知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But if we don't know exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.10,0:30:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星的具体构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the asteroid is made of,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.65,0:30:38.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么要挽救地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the effort to save the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.89,0:30:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就非常困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could go horribly wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.48,0:30:49.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星撞击的破坏性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An asteroid impact can unleash more destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.61,0:30:53.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,胜过任何一种自然灾害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than just about any other kind of natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.23,0:30:59.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它也是少数一种我们能够阻止的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's also one of the few types of nature's fury
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.19,0:31:01.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大自然灾难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we may be able to prevent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.50,0:31:08.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象在未来  一颗巨大的校行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine in the future that a huge asteroid
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.07,0:31:14.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以每小时七万英里的速度冲向地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is racing towards earth at 70,000 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.25,0:31:17.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全世界的宇航局联合起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}International space agencies have banded together
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.18,0:31:22.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发射了一枚火箭想挽救人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and launched a rocket in an effort to save mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.55,0:31:25.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,致胜的诀窍就是了解敌人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The trick is to understand the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.56,0:31:27.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星是金属质的吗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is it made of solid iron?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.19,0:31:28.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是碎岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is it made of shattered rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.60,0:31:30.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又或者是由碎石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is it made of a rubble pile,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.20,0:31:32.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或是个曾是彗星的绒球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an ex-cometary fluff ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.65,0:31:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}唐·耶蒙斯\N喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.50,0:31:35.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为如果你用一艘宇宙飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because if you hit a slab of solid iron
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.63,0:31:37.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞击一块固态铁\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.54,0:31:40.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟撞击一个绒球的反应\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's going to react far differently than an object
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.40,0:31:42.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是截然不同的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is a fluff ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.41,0:31:47.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据了解  小行星是个碎石堆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The asteroid turns out to be a rubble pile.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.85,0:31:48.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它足够柔软\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's soft enough to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.92,0:31:52.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以吸收火箭几乎全部的撞击力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mostly absorb the impact of the rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.78,0:31:56.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仍然会保持原轨道撞向地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to stay on course to collide with earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.83,0:31:59.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,体积也足够大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's also large enough
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.79,0:32:02.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会在大气层燃尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it doesn't burn up in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.49,0:32:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它击中了地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It hits,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.95,0:32:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,永远改变了地球上的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and forever changes life on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.60,0:32:15.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们不尽可能多地了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the price we could pay if we don't learn
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.51,0:32:18.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系中各种各样的小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as much as possible about the variety of asteroids
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.94,0:32:21.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就会是代价\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.88,0:32:26.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是至少对于大型小行星接近地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But at least with large asteroids,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.76,0:32:28.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会有数十年的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we should have years or decades of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.69,0:32:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,警告时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}warning about their approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.16,0:32:35.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于彗星甚至是巨大的彗星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With comets, even enormous ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.15,0:32:38.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,警告时间将以月来衡量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the warning time will be measured in months.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.24,0:32:39.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.56,0:32:42.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是乔治亚州亚特兰大的克莱顿·艾尔.\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what Clayton L. in Atlanta, Georgia
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.72,0:32:45.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想问宇宙的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wanted to ask the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.88,0:32:48.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他给我们的电子邮件中写道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, he e-mailed us:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.04,0:32:52.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么彗星撞击地球比小行星撞击地球的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Why would there be "So much less warning time" before
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.94,0:32:54.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,警告时间少那么多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an earth impact for a comet compared to an asteroid?"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.95,0:32:57.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问得好  克莱顿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Good question, Clayton.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.31,0:33:01.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们想知道什么时候会有东西撞上我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'd love to know when something might hit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.22,0:33:04.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为小行星离我们很近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turns out that asteroids are so nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.19,0:33:06.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以精确追踪它们的轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we can track their orbits precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.36,0:33:08.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就意味着我们可以精确地预测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That means we can make accurate predictions
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:10.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,未来的几十甚至几百年中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of where they will be,
